{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6685", "repo": "rails", "body": "@tarcieri I don't think any GC optimization would be significative here.\n\nFurthermore if I recall correctly, threads are implemented as processes on Linux\n\nAlso, I've made some benchmarks yesterday and using threads (pool limit of 50) and 50 processes served performed about the same with a fairly simple new Rails app. I've run something like \"ab -n 150 -c 50 http://localhost:3000/test/index\". The difference is that the multi-process approach required almost 1GB for a fresh minimal Rails app.", "_id": {"$oid": "52380552bd3543c15100c730"}, "issue_id": 6685, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6497359", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6685#issuecomment-6497359", "updated_at": "2012-06-21T23:37:00Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld", "login": "rosenfeld", "gravatar_id": "2abdb50caf0dc5b510330f68b02db8e4", "html_url": "https://github.com/rosenfeld", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2abdb50caf0dc5b510330f68b02db8e4?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F7c3aa93f86af77d8b1071d5fd2b4c91a.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 32246, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rosenfeld/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-06-21T23:37:00Z", "id": 6497359, "owner": "rails"}
